The paper deals with functional dependencies in databases, which is a topic in the field of database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of commutative integral partially ordered monoids and complete residuated lattices, which are topics in the field of abstract algebra and mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper proposes a logic for reasoning with similarity-preserving dependencies, which is a topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses computational issues and algorithms, which are topics in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses different semantics for the dependencies, which is a topic in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
